data.content:
noun
a feeling of confusion, doubt, or nervousness caused by being in a place (such as a foreign country) that is very different from what you are used to [noncount]
Foreign students often experience culture shock when they first come to the U.S. [singular]
Moving to the city was a huge culture shock for him.
cú sốc văn hóa (sự ngỡ ngànng trước một nền văn hóa khác với văn hóa của mình)
